## COMPREHENSIVE ANALYSIS: Calendar Widget View Modes & Features Migration

Based on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here's what needs to be migrated from the original Calendar Widget to TimeEntryCalendar:

---

### 1. VIEW MODES (Currently TimeEntryCalendar only has MONTH view)

The Calendar Widget supports 4 view modes defined in `types/index.ts`:

```typescript
export type ViewMode = 'monthly' | 'weekly' | 'daily' | 'agenda';
```

#### Current Implementation in Calendar.tsx (Lines 354-395):

```typescript
{/* View Mode Switcher */}
<div className="flex gap-1 bg-surface-light-elevated dark:bg-surface-dark-elevated rounded p-1">
  <button
    onClick={() => setViewMode('monthly')}
    className={`px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm transition-colors ${
      viewMode === 'monthly'
        ? 'bg-accent-blue text-white'
        : 'text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary hover:bg-surface-light dark:hover:bg-surface-dark'
    }`}
  >
    Month
  </button>
  <button
    onClick={() => setViewMode('weekly')}
    className={`px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm transition-colors ${
      viewMode === 'weekly'
        ? 'bg-accent-blue text-white'
        : 'text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary hover:bg-surface-light dark:hover:bg-surface-dark'
    }`}
  >
    Week
  </button>
  <button
    onClick={() => setViewMode('daily')}
    className={`px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm transition-colors ${
      viewMode === 'daily'
        ? 'bg-accent-blue text-white'
        : 'text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary hover:bg-surface-light dark:hover:bg-surface-dark'
    }`}
  >
    Day
  </button>
  <button
    onClick={() => setViewMode('agenda')}
    className={`px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm transition-colors ${
      viewMode === 'agenda'
        ? 'bg-accent-blue text-white'
        : 'text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary hover:bg-surface-light dark:hover:bg-surface-dark'
    }`}
  >
    List
  </button>
</div>
```

---

### 2. HOW VIEW MODES ARE IMPLEMENTED (Conditional Rendering)

In Calendar.tsx (Lines 418-486), the views are conditionally rendered:

```typescript
{viewMode === 'monthly' ? (
  <MonthView
    currentDate={currentDate}
    events={expandedEvents}
    tasks={tasks}
    onDayClick={handleDayClick}
  />
) : viewMode === 'weekly' ? (
  <WeekView
    currentDate={currentDate}
    events={expandedEvents}
    tasks={tasks}
    onDayClick={handleDayClick}
    onEventClick={(event, dateKey) => {
      setSelectedDateKey(dateKey);
      setNewEventTitle(event.title);
      setNewEventDescription(event.description || '');
      setIsAllDay(event.isAllDay !== false);
      setStartTime(event.startTime || '09:00');
      setEndTime(event.endTime || '10:00');
      setEditingEventId(event.id);
      setIsModalOpen(true);
    }}
    showTimeSlots={true}
  />
) : viewMode === 'daily' ? (
  <DayView
    date={currentDate}
    events={expandedEvents[format(currentDate, 'yyyy-MM-dd')] || []}
    onEventClick={(event, dateKey) => {
      setSelectedDateKey(dateKey);
      setNewEventTitle(event.title);
      setNewEventDescription(event.description || '');
      setIsAllDay(event.isAllDay !== false);
      setStartTime(event.startTime || '09:00');
      setEndTime(event.endTime || '10:00');
      setEditingEventId(event.id);
      setIsModalOpen(true);
    }}
    onTimeSlotClick={(hour) => {
      const dateKey = format(currentDate, 'yyyy-MM-dd');
      setSelectedDateKey(dateKey);
      setNewEventTitle('');
      setNewEventDescription('');
      setEditingEventId(null);
      setIsAllDay(false);
      setStartTime(`${hour.toString().padStart(2, '0')}:00`);
